
1. Project Goal (one clear sentence)
To create a comprehensive digital ecosystem that allows users to discover and purchase products and services while providing a searchable directory for businesses and factories to showcase their operations.
2. Target Users
Customers: Individuals looking to buy products or book services.
Business Owners/Sellers: Small to medium enterprises looking to sell and gain visibility.
Factory Managers: Industrial entities seeking to list their facilities for B2B partnerships.
Administrators: Users who manage listings and moderate the platform.
3. Main Features
Searchable Directory: Advanced filters to find businesses and factories by category, location, and rating.
E-commerce Marketplace: A functional shopping cart and checkout system for products and services.
Detailed Listings: Rich profiles for businesses and factories including photos, descriptions, and contact info.
Inquiry System: A lead generation form for users to contact factories or service providers directly.
Review & Rating System: User-generated feedback for all listings.
4. Pages / Layout
Home: Featured listings, trending products, and a prominent search bar.
Marketplace: A grid view of products and services with category sidebars.
Directory: A list or map view of registered businesses and factories.
Product/Listing Detail Page: Comprehensive view of a single item or business.
User Dashboard: For buyers to track orders and for sellers to manage their listings.
Login/Registration: Secure entry points for different user roles.
5. UI Style Requirements
Professional & Trustworthy: Use a clean, corporate color palette (e.g., Navy Blue, Slate Grey, and White).
Modern & Responsive: Fully functional on mobile, tablet, and desktop.
Data-Driven: Clear typography and organized tables/grids for easy comparison of business data.
6. State Management Needs
Context API: To handle global state such as user authentication status, shopping cart items, and persistent search filters across pages.
7. Authentication Needs
Multi-Role Auth: Users must be able to sign up as either a "Buyer" or a "Partner" (Business/Factory).
Protected Routes: Dashboards and listing management pages should only be accessible to logged-in users with the correct permissions.
8. Design Constraints
Mobile-First Design: Ensure the directory is easy to navigate on smartphones.
Tech Stack: Must be built using React for the frontend and Supabase for the database and authentication.
Performance: Fast loading times for image-heavy business listings
